---
import Base from "../layouts/lilybaseweb.astro";
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — Lily">
  <style>
    .policy-container {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 5rem auto;
      padding: 0 2rem;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    
    .policy-container h1 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--pink-mid);
    }

    .policy-meta {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    
    .policy-container h2 {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .policy-container p {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 300;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }
    
    .policy-container ul {
      margin-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    
    .policy-container li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="policy-container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="policy-meta">Last Updated: June 16, 2026</p>

    <p>
      Your privacy is highly important to us. This Privacy Policy details how Lily ("we", "our", or "the bot") processes and protects server data and user information.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      To provide moderation and protection features, Lily processes the following guild details:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>User IDs & Usernames:</strong> Stored to track warnings/strikes and handle mutes, kicks, or bans.</li>
      <li><strong>Guild Settings & Channels:</strong> Custom prefixes, configuration thresholds, and moderation log channel IDs are cached and stored in our local secure database.</li>
      <li><strong>Automod Content Processing:</strong> Messages are analyzed in real-time to detect spam links and bad words. This processing occurs in memory and message contents are <strong>never stored</strong> unless a violation is recorded in the moderation audit log.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Data Usage</h2>
    <p>
      The processed data is used solely to configure moderation parameters for your Discord server. We do not sell, rent, or distribute any user or server statistics to third-party advertisers or analytics platforms.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Warning strikes and moderation history remain stored in our local database for moderation audit purposes. Server administrators can clear server records at any time. If you wish to request the manual removal of your Discord data from our database, please contact us through our support channel.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to modify this privacy statement at any time. Any changes will be posted here on our website. Continued use of the bot constitutes agreement to our privacy terms.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
